Combine cut and awk â€“ Extract & Analyze EC2 Instance Data
cut -d ',' -f3,4 ec2_instances.csv | awk -F ',' '{count[$2]++} END {for (zone in count) print zone, count[zone]}'

Combine cut and sed â€“ Clean & Format IAM User Report
cut -d ',' -f1,5 iam_users.csv | sed '1d'
ğŸ§° More Useful Combinations (Real-Life Cloud Scenarios)
ğŸ” Get Users Without MFA from IAM Report
cut -d ',' -f1,4 iam_users.csv | awk -F ',' '$2 == "false" {print $1}'

ğŸ›¡ï¸ Extract Failed SSH IPs and Clean Output
grep "Failed password" auth.log | cut -d ' ' -f11 | sed 's/[^0-9\.]//g'

ğŸ“„ Extract EC2 IDs & Status, Then Format to ID=STATUS
cut -d ',' -f1,6 ec2_instances.csv | sed 's/,/=/'


ğŸ”„ Bonus: Combine cut, awk, and sed
âš™ï¸ Task: Show usernames of console users without MFA, clean header, and format
cut -d ',' -f1,4,5 iam_users.csv | sed '1d' | awk -F ',' '$2 == "false" && $3 == "true" {print $1}'




